refactor: model marketplace as graph + DAG constructs

Replace flat data/stream declarations in marketplace_streams.fl with:
- graph marketplace_registry: typed nodes (ComponentNode, PublisherNode,
  ReviewNode, LicenseNode), CSR storage, real-time overlays
  (download_count, rating, security), ai_feed for recommendations,
  StreamSight observe for anomaly detection
- dag component_dependencies: enforce acyclic for cycle detection,
  topo_sort for installation ordering, version_conflict overlay
- series on both constructs for tamper-proof audit trail
  (Merkle-chained, MTP-timestamped, lattice-imprinted, PoVC-attested)

Streams are now lattice topic projections of graph state, not the
primary data model. Data declarations and circuits retained for
wire format and operation definitions.

Update canonical spec ¬ß5 to describe graph-based data model and
refactor ¬ß6.4 version resolution to reference DAG operations.

